						<p>Personally i like turkey roasted on its own on a trivet in a baking tray, cavity filled with stock and sealed with a skewer, covered in greaseproof paper to protect the skin then foil. This means your turkey meat does not dry out. Adding stuffings etc causes more drying out in the bird. Using the greaseproof paper means you get an even colouring all over when you take it the foil and paper off for the last 50 mins of cooking. Sometimes simple is best.												</p>
						</div>
		
						<div class="comment-bubble-btn">
						</div>								
						
